1
00:00:00,790 --> 00:00:03,630
[Episode 33]

2
00:00:03,630 --> 00:00:08,940
Dad! I heard my birth mother is still alive.

3
00:00:08,940 --> 00:00:13,610
Then why did you lie to me that she was dead? Why?

4
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:18,020
What?

5
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:29,630
Dan Dan, what are you saying now?

6
00:00:29,630 --> 00:00:33,890
Your mother is dead. Who says that?

7
00:00:33,890 --> 00:00:36,260
I met our old neighbor Ajumma.

8
00:00:36,260 --> 00:00:38,520
She told me that.

9
00:00:38,520 --> 00:00:42,140
That my mother came looking for me when I was 5 years old.

10
00:00:42,140 --> 00:00:46,680
She said she saw my mom!

11
00:00:46,680 --> 00:00:49,800
- What?
- How can you do this to me?

12
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:52,920
You split up with my mom by cheating with my step-mom.

13
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:56,860
How can you not let me see my mom as well?

14
00:00:56,860 --> 00:00:59,020
Dan Dan, calm down. And listen to me.

15
00:00:59,020 --> 00:01:05,460
No. Just tell me if my mom is alive or dead.

16
00:01:05,460 --> 00:01:09,200
Is my mom alive? Is that right?

17
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:13,560
No. That lady got something wrong.

18
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:18,480
Your mother is a dead person. Think that she is dead.

19
00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:22,130
What?

20
00:01:22,130 --> 00:01:27,060
Did you just say I should think that she is dead?

21
00:01:27,060 --> 00:01:34,620
How can I think my mom is dead when she is alive?

22
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:42,760
Dad. How can you separate me from my mom like this? Do you hate her that much?

23
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:46,720
Yes! I hate her! So just think she's dead.

24
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:51,730
No, that woman is dead!

25
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:02,600
No matter how much you hate my birth mother,

26
00:02:02,600 --> 00:02:07,630
how can you say that she is dead when she's not?

27
00:02:09,860 --> 00:02:12,530
I will never forgive you, Dad.

28
00:02:12,530 --> 00:02:18,960
I cannot forgive you until death. I'll never see you again. I am not your daughter anymore!

29
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,370
Dan Dan. Dan Dan!

30
00:02:21,370 --> 00:02:26,180
How can you say that to your dad?

31
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:29,550
What is all this?

32
00:02:29,550 --> 00:02:35,310
How did that old neighbor woman meet Dan Dan?

33
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:41,650
Honey. Shall I see Dan Dan and tell her everything?

34
00:02:41,650 --> 00:02:44,660
Please stay out of this.

35
00:02:55,410 --> 00:02:58,910
I should meet that Ajumeoni again.

36
00:02:58,910 --> 00:03:01,100
That way, I will know what happened to my mom.

37
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:04,030
But where is she?

38
00:03:07,230 --> 00:03:13,340
Dan Dan. Dan Dan!

39
00:03:13,340 --> 00:03:16,070
Dan Dan!

40
00:03:21,880 --> 00:03:25,470
The woman who lived here 15 years ago?

41
00:03:25,470 --> 00:03:28,130
Yes. That Ajumeoni.

42
00:03:28,130 --> 00:03:30,370
Can I get her contact information?

43
00:03:30,370 --> 00:03:32,280
Well...

44
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:37,830
When I came here 6 years ago, the owner was a grandmother. Is it her?

45
00:03:37,830 --> 00:03:41,720
She's not an old lady but a middle-aged woman.

46
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:44,840
I don't know then.

47
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:51,000
Then, can I get that grandmother's contact information?

48
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:58,790
I have to meet that Ajumeoni from 15 years ago.

49
00:03:58,790 --> 00:04:01,530
It's to search for my mom.

50
00:04:01,530 --> 00:04:05,350
Alright. I will look for her and let you know.

51
00:04:05,350 --> 00:04:08,240
Don't worry too much.

52
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:11,070
Thank you. Thank you so much!

53
00:04:11,070 --> 00:04:13,680
Please help me. Please.

54
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,020
Okay, okay.

55
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:17,530
Thank you!

56
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:28,370
I should have asked for that Ajumeoni's phone number.

57
00:04:28,370 --> 00:04:30,320
What do I do now?

58
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:33,690
How do I search for my mother?

59
00:04:45,540 --> 00:04:49,980
Driver Park. What brings you here?

60
00:04:49,980 --> 00:04:52,300
Hello.

61
00:04:52,300 --> 00:04:56,570
Actually, I couldn't contact Dan Dan.

62
00:04:56,570 --> 00:04:58,300
Is she inside?

63
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:02,290
No. Ms. Park is not home right now.

64
00:05:02,290 --> 00:05:04,010
Is she not home?

65
00:05:04,010 --> 00:05:07,980
No. She asked me to look after the kids as she has some sudden issue.

66
00:05:07,980 --> 00:05:10,560
I was wondering what's going on as well.

67
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:13,560
Did something happen to her?

68
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:17,230
No, it's nothing.

69
00:05:17,230 --> 00:05:20,560
Ajumeoni, I am sorry,

70
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:24,780
but can you ask her to call me once she's back? Please.

71
00:05:24,780 --> 00:05:27,690
Yes. I will.

72
00:05:27,690 --> 00:05:30,540
Then, goodbye.

73
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:38,670
Chairman. Welcome home.

74
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:40,080
Yes.

75
00:05:40,080 --> 00:05:44,120
But isn't that person Driver Park?

76
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:47,070
Yes. It is him.

77
00:05:47,070 --> 00:05:49,950
Ms. Park stepped out for some important work.

78
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:53,040
Driver Park came as he couldn't contact her.

79
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:55,720
I think something happened to Ms. Park.

80
00:05:55,720 --> 00:06:00,440
Looking at Driver Park's face, it seems like big trouble.

81
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:02,760
Big trouble?

82
00:06:09,220 --> 00:06:13,460
Yes! I hate her! So just think she's dead.

83
00:06:13,460 --> 00:06:17,650
No, that woman is dead.

84
00:06:20,430 --> 00:06:23,640
Why does he hate my mom so much?

85
00:06:23,640 --> 00:06:29,130
Even so, how can he say she's dead when she's not?

86
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:34,690
I will find her, at least now.

87
00:06:34,710 --> 00:06:38,250
No matter what.

88
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:43,710
Oh my, Dan Dan!

89
00:06:43,710 --> 00:06:47,700
Why are you not picking up your father's calls? Do you know how worried he was?

90
00:06:47,700 --> 00:06:51,370
Aigo... My Dan Dan's hands are frozen.

91
00:06:51,370 --> 00:06:54,390
I guess you wandered around a lot.

92
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:58,790
Where is my dad? I have to say something to him.

93
00:06:58,790 --> 00:07:02,670
Honey! Dan Dan is here.

94
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,960
Dan Dan.

95
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,710
Where were you?

96
00:07:06,710 --> 00:07:10,140
Dad. I have to tell you something.

97
00:07:10,140 --> 00:07:13,430
Yes, yes. Sit down first.

98
00:07:13,430 --> 00:07:17,660
You should tell him if you have something to say to him.

99
00:07:24,670 --> 00:07:33,250
Mom and Dad, thank you for raising me well until now.

100
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:35,990
And you both love each other.

101
00:07:35,990 --> 00:07:39,050
People who love each other should live together.

102
00:07:39,050 --> 00:07:42,320
I understand you both now.

103
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:48,120
When I was young, I rudely said that you two had an affair and abandoned my birth mom.

104
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:51,720
I'm sorry about saying it thoughtlessly.

105
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:54,350
I apologize.

106
00:07:57,540 --> 00:08:05,230
I will not say anything to you both anymore,

107
00:08:05,230 --> 00:08:12,100
so please tell me my birth mom's name.

108
00:08:12,100 --> 00:08:16,660
I want to find my mother, at least now. I beg of you.

109
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:17,990
What?

110
00:08:17,990 --> 00:08:23,420
Dad, tell me everything you know about my mom.

111
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:26,620
How old is she? Where is her hometown?

112
00:08:26,620 --> 00:08:29,310
Which school did she go to?

113
00:08:29,310 --> 00:08:32,650
If you don't know her resident number, just...

114
00:08:32,650 --> 00:08:38,190
just tell me her age. I will not resent you two anymore.

115
00:08:38,190 --> 00:08:42,310
I will be grateful to you for the rest of my life.

116
00:08:42,310 --> 00:08:47,820
The neighbor Ajumma told me that my mom had gone to the US. Is that true?

117
00:08:47,820 --> 00:08:50,260
Do you know where in the US?

118
00:08:50,260 --> 00:08:54,060
Dan Dan, why are you acting like this?

119
00:08:54,060 --> 00:08:58,150
Mom, Grandmother, please tell me.

120
00:08:58,150 --> 00:09:00,480
Please.

121
00:09:02,630 --> 00:09:06,710
Dan Dan, your mother is dead.

122
00:09:06,710 --> 00:09:08,620
That Ajumma is wrong.

123
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:10,790
She told you the wrong thing.

124
00:09:10,790 --> 00:09:17,430
That Ajumma told me that my mom came to see me when I was five years old!

125
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:22,710
Then why are you lying to me!

126
00:09:22,710 --> 00:09:24,780
I said she's dead!

127
00:09:24,780 --> 00:09:27,320
Why don't you believe your dad but trust a stranger's words?

128
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:31,250
That woman is dead!

129
00:09:31,250 --> 00:09:35,740
Okay. I get it.

130
00:09:35,740 --> 00:09:38,850
Please tell me my mom's name, at least.

131
00:09:38,850 --> 00:09:42,280
Tell me her age, at least.

132
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:47,090
I don't know anything about her. I erased everything.

133
00:09:47,090 --> 00:09:50,160
Dad.

134
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:53,570
Why are you acting like this?

135
00:09:53,570 --> 00:09:59,050
If my mother is dead, why don't you tell me her name?

136
00:09:59,050 --> 00:10:04,440
Is she a criminal? Is she in prison?

137
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:09,580
Dad, even if my mom is in prison,

138
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:11,690
I want to see her face.

139
00:10:11,690 --> 00:10:16,270
I want to see how she looks, even if it's her shadow! So, please, Dad!

140
00:10:16,270 --> 00:10:18,300
She is a dead woman!

141
00:10:18,300 --> 00:10:23,720
So don't talk about her anymore.

142
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:25,700
Will you not tell me even if we cut our ties?

143
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:31,180
If you don't tell me about my mom, I will cut ties with you.

144
00:10:31,180 --> 00:10:32,680
What?

145
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:35,570
Still? Will you not tell me?

146
00:10:35,570 --> 00:10:38,220
Sure! Let's cut ties.

147
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:41,790
Even if that happens, I will never tell you!

148
00:10:43,690 --> 00:10:46,130
Okay! I get it!

149
00:10:46,130 --> 00:10:51,470
I'm not your daughter anymore from today!

150
00:10:51,470 --> 00:10:54,260
Aigoo...

151
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:57,340
What is all this?

152
00:10:57,340 --> 00:11:00,210
I cannot forgive him. I will not forgive him.

153
00:11:00,210 --> 00:11:05,190
I will not see him ever again.

154
00:11:05,190 --> 00:11:12,790
But how do I find my mom now? My mom...

155
00:11:12,790 --> 00:11:14,880
You grew up just like your mom.

156
00:11:14,880 --> 00:11:18,210
Do you see your biological mother often?

157
00:11:18,210 --> 00:11:22,230
- My birth mom?
- Yes. She came to see you once.

158
00:11:22,230 --> 00:11:24,300
Didn't you see her after that?

159
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:28,870
Well, she went to America, so she can't come often.

160
00:11:28,870 --> 00:11:30,660
America...

161
00:11:30,660 --> 00:11:35,660
That's right. She told me my mom is in the US.

162
00:11:43,460 --> 00:11:46,880
CEO. CEO Anna.

163
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:52,550
Ms. Park, why are you here at this time?

164
00:11:52,550 --> 00:11:55,850
I have to tell you something.

165
00:11:55,850 --> 00:12:01,900
Can you give me some time? Please?

166
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:04,630
Ms. Park, what's wrong?

167
00:12:11,570 --> 00:12:14,550
Ms. Park, please drink. It's warm chamomile tea.

168
00:12:14,550 --> 00:12:17,170
Thank you.

169
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:28,870
CEO, what happened to your face?

170
00:12:28,870 --> 00:12:34,160
Oh... I just fell down and hurt myself.

171
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:36,170
It's healed now.

172
00:12:36,170 --> 00:12:38,680
Oh, okay...

173
00:12:41,590 --> 00:12:44,630
But, what is the matter?

174
00:12:44,630 --> 00:12:47,940
I told you I would not be in Seoul for a while.

175
00:12:47,940 --> 00:12:51,480
Why did you come without notice? You could've missed me.

176
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,150
CEO.

177
00:12:53,150 --> 00:12:55,720
I'm sorry for coming this late at night.

178
00:12:55,720 --> 00:13:03,340
But you are the only person I have.

179
00:13:03,340 --> 00:13:06,260
Actually...

180
00:13:06,260 --> 00:13:11,080
I heard that my mother is alive.

181
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:12,370
What?

182
00:13:12,370 --> 00:13:17,600
Until now, I thought my birth mother was dead.

183
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:22,630
But, she is in the US. I want to search for her from now on.

184
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:25,150
But I don't know anyone in the US.

185
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:28,700
With the feeling of clutching at a straw, I came to see you.

186
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:33,810
I heard we can search through the Korean Association.

187
00:13:33,810 --> 00:13:37,880
The person who gave birth to Park Dan Dan 27 years ago.

188
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:41,600
Who lived in Sanggye-dong.

189
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:45,180
June 30th is her daughter's birthday.

190
00:13:45,180 --> 00:13:49,820
Would it be hard to find her with these?

191
00:13:49,820 --> 00:13:56,550
Well, I don't know what you're saying suddenly.

192
00:13:56,550 --> 00:14:01,270
I don't think we can find her with that.

193
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:07,920
My dad won't even tell me my mom's name or not even a thing.

194
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:13,250
He had an affair with my step-mom, and he abandoned my birth mother.

195
00:14:13,250 --> 00:14:17,690
And he lied to me that my birth mom was dead.

196
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:23,050
I don't understand him and cannot forgive him also.

197
00:14:23,050 --> 00:14:28,220
I will cut my ties with my dad. I hate him.

198
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:32,950
CEO, what do I do?

199
00:14:32,950 --> 00:14:38,050
Ms. Park, I am sorry. I don't know anyone from the Korean Association.

200
00:14:38,050 --> 00:14:43,330
I don't think I can help you with these things. Then excuse me, I have work.

201
00:14:43,330 --> 00:14:45,730
CEO...

202
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:53,990
What do I do?

203
00:14:53,990 --> 00:15:00,050
How am I going to find my mom?

204
00:15:11,560 --> 00:15:15,090
What is all this?

205
00:15:15,090 --> 00:15:19,620
Why is she resenting her dad when I'm the one who abandoned her?

206
00:15:19,620 --> 00:15:23,940
Dan Dan, that's not right...

207
00:15:26,180 --> 00:15:30,390
What will you do finding this bad mom?

208
00:15:30,390 --> 00:15:35,850
What do I do? My poor Dan Dan.

209
00:16:19,590 --> 00:16:22,300
Hello.

210
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:26,180
Soo Chul, can you see me for a moment?

211
00:16:26,180 --> 00:16:30,310
Dan Dan came looking for me.

212
00:16:30,310 --> 00:16:33,330
She wants to search for her mom in the US.

213
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:37,380
What?

214
00:16:37,380 --> 00:16:41,350
What did you say to her?

215
00:16:41,350 --> 00:16:44,570
I didn't tell her anything.

216
00:16:44,570 --> 00:16:47,990
To me...

217
00:16:47,990 --> 00:16:52,890
She told me her mom is alive in the US.

218
00:16:52,890 --> 00:16:57,900
And she asked me to look for her mom through Korean Association.

219
00:16:59,870 --> 00:17:04,570
But I rejected her, saying I couldn't do that.

220
00:17:06,890 --> 00:17:10,320
Nobody knows that I am Kim Ji Young.

221
00:17:10,320 --> 00:17:14,920
Nobody other than Chairman Lee knows that.

222
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:17,900
Dan Dan will never find me.

223
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:23,020
So, don't worry, Soo Chul.

224
00:17:23,020 --> 00:17:28,100
At least now, tell her the truth.

225
00:17:28,100 --> 00:17:31,750
It's me who abandoned her.

226
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,870
I'm the one who committed the sin.

227
00:17:33,870 --> 00:17:38,400
But why are you being resented by Dan Dan?

228
00:17:38,400 --> 00:17:43,890
I am the one who did wrong. But why do you have to be hated by her?

229
00:17:43,890 --> 00:17:48,090
You did nothing wrong.

230
00:17:48,090 --> 00:17:51,720
So, tell everything to Dan Dan. Everything.

231
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:56,390
That way, she won't look for this bad mom.

232
00:17:59,010 --> 00:18:07,160
Are you saying I should tell Dan Dan that her mom abandoned her?

233
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:13,890
Do you still not know why I didn't tell her that?

234
00:18:13,890 --> 00:18:20,110
Do you want to see her heart bleed?

235
00:18:20,110 --> 00:18:26,030
Now, do you understand what you have done?

236
00:18:26,030 --> 00:18:29,470
I did wrong...

237
00:18:29,470 --> 00:18:34,610
I was wrong. I made a mistake.

238
00:18:37,280 --> 00:18:40,100
If you know that,

239
00:18:40,100 --> 00:18:44,620
then disappear from our lives.

240
00:18:44,620 --> 00:18:47,150
As quickly as possible.

241
00:19:04,320 --> 00:19:08,010
Gyeonwoo and Jingnyuh were able to meet again

242
00:19:08,010 --> 00:19:13,030
on the bridge built by the magpies and crows.

243
00:19:13,030 --> 00:19:16,590
[Gyeonwoo and Jingnyuh]

244
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:57,610
Young lady, are you not getting off?

245
00:19:57,620 --> 00:20:00,540
Excuse me?

246
00:20:00,540 --> 00:20:04,060
Oh, I'm sorry.

247
00:20:04,060 --> 00:20:06,510
But, where is this place?

248
00:20:06,510 --> 00:20:09,830
This is the last stop.

249
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:21,450
Why did I come this far?

250
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:28,300
[Taxi Service: Calling for a cab]

251
00:20:36,190 --> 00:20:39,610
[Reservation Failed]
[Retry]

252
00:20:45,560 --> 00:20:49,350
What do I do? There's no taxi also.

253
00:20:49,350 --> 00:20:52,360
[Chairman]

254
00:20:54,310 --> 00:20:55,690
Hello, Chairman.

255
00:20:55,690 --> 00:20:59,100
Ms. Park, where are you now?

256
00:20:59,100 --> 00:21:02,440
You are still not home. Is something wrong?

257
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:09,380
The truth is... I'm at the last stop for bus number 699.

258
00:21:09,380 --> 00:21:16,820
I took the bus, but I stayed on the bus without realizing it until the last stop.

259
00:21:16,820 --> 00:21:21,240
But it looks like the last bus has left.

260
00:21:21,240 --> 00:21:23,700
All the lights are off on the buses.

261
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:26,170
I can't get hold of a taxi also.

262
