00:58:48,680 --> 00:58:56,150
I don't know how she could abandon her own baby.

793
00:58:56,200 --> 00:59:01,100
I don't want to find the woman who abandoned me.

794
00:59:01,100 --> 00:59:07,140
So please stop searching for my mom.

795
00:59:15,000 --> 00:59:19,160
Ms. Park, where are you now?

796
00:59:19,160 --> 00:59:22,260
Can we meet?

797
00:59:27,800 --> 00:59:30,690
Ms. Park. Steaks are good here.

798
00:59:30,690 --> 00:59:33,170
Please try some.

799
00:59:33,170 --> 00:59:35,620
I can do it myself.

800
00:59:35,620 --> 00:59:38,570
Who cares who cuts it? You just have to enjoy it.

801
00:59:38,570 --> 00:59:40,540
Please, go ahead.

802
00:59:40,540 --> 00:59:43,340
Thank you.

803
00:59:43,340 --> 00:59:50,470
But Chairman. Why are you buying me things like this, suddenly?

804
00:59:54,140 --> 00:59:57,100
You seem to be going through a hard time.

805
00:59:57,100 --> 00:59:59,820
So I wanted to cheer you up with this food.

806
00:59:59,820 --> 01:00:01,940
As someone who lives in the same house,

807
01:00:01,940 --> 01:00:06,660
I can't ignore it when you're having a hard time.

808
01:00:06,660 --> 01:00:13,300
So please eat this, and be the strong Ms. Park that you are.

809
01:00:16,790 --> 01:00:24,460
Chairman, I'm sorry to show you that I am depressed due to a personal matter.

810
01:00:24,460 --> 01:00:27,640
As you said, I will eat this

811
01:00:27,640 --> 01:00:32,080
and show you my strong side starting tomorrow.

812
01:00:38,040 --> 01:00:41,510
It's really delicious. Please eat, too.

813
01:00:41,510 --> 01:00:43,700
Okay.

814
01:01:01,490 --> 01:01:04,600
Chairman, where are we going now?

815
01:01:04,600 --> 01:01:08,120
Our house is in the opposite direction.

816
01:01:08,120 --> 01:01:09,720
Since we are out here,

817
01:01:09,720 --> 01:01:11,720
why don't we go for some beer?

818
01:01:11,720 --> 01:01:14,260
There is a great craft beer pub nearby.

819
01:01:14,260 --> 01:01:17,730
Let's drink a glass of beer and become strong!

820
01:01:17,730 --> 01:01:22,440
The steak you bought for me is more than enough.

821
01:01:22,440 --> 01:01:25,330
I am really okay now.

822
01:01:25,330 --> 01:01:28,430
I know you like beer.

823
01:01:28,430 --> 01:01:30,450
I'm craving a nice cold beer myself.

824
01:01:30,450 --> 01:01:33,500
It's right in front over there. Let's go.

825
01:01:45,770 --> 01:01:47,440
What do you think? Isn't it good?

826
01:01:47,440 --> 01:01:49,950
Yes, it's very smooth and delicious.

827
01:01:49,950 --> 01:01:53,370
See? Aren't you glad you came?

828
01:01:57,960 --> 01:02:04,160
Okay, we're about to throw a special event for the 5th anniversary of the store!

829
01:02:04,200 --> 01:02:08,130
Hello, everyone. Thank you for coming to our store today.

830
01:02:08,130 --> 01:02:12,830
The special event to mark the 5th anniversary of the store opening is

831
01:02:12,830 --> 01:02:17,500
a contest of drinking 1000cc of our beer!

832
01:02:20,720 --> 01:02:25,650
I'll show you the prize for the winner tonight.

833
01:02:25,650 --> 01:02:30,820
The one who gets the first place will get this cute teddy bear

834
01:02:30,820 --> 01:02:35,800
and 5 coupons for free beers!

835
01:02:39,090 --> 01:02:48,750
From now on, please come to the front who wants to participate in the beer-drinking contest!

836
01:02:48,750 --> 01:02:51,190
Please come out!

837
01:02:51,190 --> 01:02:54,660
Please come out!

838
01:02:54,660 --> 01:02:57,650
Please don't hesitate and come forward!

839
01:02:57,650 --> 01:03:00,680
[A special event for the 5th anniversary of the store: Beer-drinking contest]

840
01:03:00,680 --> 01:03:04,090
That teddy bear is so cute.

841
01:03:06,190 --> 01:03:08,710
Ms. Park. Do you like that teddy bear?

842
01:03:08,710 --> 01:03:10,920
Do you want it?

843
01:03:10,920 --> 01:03:13,610
Yes, I do, but...

844
01:03:13,610 --> 01:03:16,990
Ms. Park. I will win that teddy bear for you.

845
01:03:16,990 --> 01:03:19,730
No, it's okay. I was just saying.

846
01:03:19,730 --> 01:03:23,600
Up until this gentleman! No more participation!

847
01:03:23,600 --> 01:03:25,980
That's it!

848
01:03:25,980 --> 01:03:32,600
When I say "fighting," you can start to drink. Please give us a round of applause!

849
01:03:32,600 --> 01:03:36,630
The gentleman over there is too excited!

850
01:03:36,630 --> 01:03:38,780
Get ready. The beer-drinking contest!

851
01:03:38,780 --> 01:03:41,800
Fighting!

852
01:03:45,810 --> 01:03:48,690
Number one and two drop out!

853
01:03:48,690 --> 01:03:52,260
Okay, number three to five! You got this!

854
01:03:52,260 --> 01:03:54,860
Fighting! Fighting!

855
01:03:54,860 --> 01:03:56,940
Fighting!

856
01:03:56,940 --> 01:03:58,850
Number four drops out!

857
01:03:58,850 --> 01:04:03,320
- It's number three or five!
- Chairman, fighting!

858
01:04:03,320 --> 01:04:06,670
Number three! Number five!

859
01:04:14,890 --> 01:04:17,440
Wow, you got the first place of the day!

860
01:04:17,440 --> 01:04:21,270
Why don't you go up here?

861
01:04:30,010 --> 01:04:33,590
He got the grand prize of the night!

862
01:04:38,790 --> 01:04:42,720
Ms. Park. Do you like that teddy bear that much?

863
01:04:42,720 --> 01:04:47,160
Yes, it's very cute.

864
01:04:47,190 --> 01:04:49,810
But I should give this to Se Jong.

865
01:04:49,810 --> 01:04:53,020
He will like it too.

866
01:04:53,020 --> 01:04:54,890
Se Jong has lots of dolls.

867
01:04:54,890 --> 01:04:57,960
And Se Jong likes robots more than teddy bears.

868
01:04:57,960 --> 01:05:00,170
If he wants the teddy bear,

869
01:05:00,170 --> 01:05:05,050
I will buy him separately. So please keep this one.

870
01:05:05,050 --> 01:05:07,230
When you go through a hard time like now,

871
01:05:07,230 --> 01:05:10,030
you can hug the teddy bear and get consoled.

872
01:05:10,030 --> 01:05:12,610
Chairman.

873
01:05:16,690 --> 01:05:19,470
Ms. Park.

874
01:05:19,470 --> 01:05:23,450
I hope you don't think anything else from this.

875
01:05:23,450 --> 01:05:28,320
Even between friends, when difficult things happen, they help each other.

876
01:05:28,320 --> 01:05:33,800
So please don't put any special meaning to it.

877
01:05:33,800 --> 01:05:37,240
Chairman. You don't have to worry about me anymore.

878
01:05:37,240 --> 01:05:40,130
I am really okay.

879
01:05:40,130 --> 01:05:45,250
From tomorrow, I will go back to the strong Ms. Park.

880
01:06:10,810 --> 01:06:14,770
Chairman. You don't have to worry about me anymore.

881
01:06:14,770 --> 01:06:21,110
From tomorrow, I will go back to the strong Ms. Park.

882
01:06:21,110 --> 01:06:23,770
Right.

883
01:06:23,770 --> 01:06:28,170
Ms. Park will be really okay now, won't she?

884
01:06:32,180 --> 01:06:34,460
Ms. Park--

885
01:06:34,490 --> 01:06:36,380
What?

886
01:06:36,380 --> 01:06:40,400
Where did she go at this early in the morning?

887
01:06:46,140 --> 01:06:50,270
Ajumeoni, why were you upstairs at this hour?

888
01:06:50,270 --> 01:06:52,870
I had to go home first thing this morning.

889
01:06:52,870 --> 01:06:56,130
So I went to see Ms. Park to ask for help with the breakfast.

890
01:06:56,130 --> 01:06:59,360
But she's not there. And the room is all cleaned up.

891
01:06:59,360 --> 01:07:01,090
At this early in the morning?

892
01:07:01,090 --> 01:07:03,000
Why don't you call her?

893
01:07:03,000 --> 01:07:05,710
She left her phone in the room.

894
01:07:05,710 --> 01:07:07,850
What?

895
01:07:07,850 --> 01:07:12,700
She's never done this before. Where did she go?

896
01:07:20,710 --> 01:07:23,580
Ms. Park!

897
01:07:26,030 --> 01:07:29,120
Ms. Park!

898
01:07:31,320 --> 01:07:34,280
Ms. Park!

899
01:07:38,260 --> 01:07:42,760
Ms. Park!

900
01:07:42,760 --> 01:07:45,770
Ms. Park!

901
01:07:50,560 --> 01:07:54,930
Ms. Park!

902
01:07:54,930 --> 01:07:58,190
Ms. Park!

903
01:08:03,710 --> 01:08:06,620
Chairman.

904
01:08:11,370 --> 01:08:15,020
Ms. Park. Where have you been this early in the morning?

905
01:08:15,020 --> 01:08:17,510
I've been looking for you for a while.

906
01:08:17,510 --> 01:08:23,050
Are you alright, Ms. Park?

907
01:08:23,100 --> 01:08:25,310
Yes.

908
01:08:25,310 --> 01:08:30,030
As you said, I was going to be the strong Ms. Park from today,

909
01:08:30,030 --> 01:08:33,100
so I went for a walk.

910
01:08:35,650 --> 01:08:39,210
But Chairman, in this cold weather,

911
01:08:39,210 --> 01:08:42,850
you didn't dress enough.

912
01:08:42,870 --> 01:08:50,690
Were you looking for me because you were worried?

913
01:08:52,720 --> 01:08:58,600
It's because you left without your phone at this hour.

914
01:09:02,200 --> 01:09:04,060
Chairman.

915
01:09:04,060 --> 01:09:07,190
You told me not to cross the line,

916
01:09:07,190 --> 01:09:10,110
and why do you keep crossing it yourself?

917
01:09:10,110 --> 01:09:16,130
You've crossed the line just now.

918
01:09:16,130 --> 01:09:20,150
What... What did you say?

919
01:09:20,150 --> 01:09:24,990
Are you the only one allowed to cross the line?

920
01:09:27,140 --> 01:09:29,620
Ms. Park.

921
01:09:34,130 --> 01:09:39,350
♫ That phrase I love you ♫

922
01:09:39,350 --> 01:09:44,390
♫ I couldn't say enough ♫

923
01:09:44,390 --> 01:09:49,430
♫ As much as I missed you all night long ♫

924
01:09:49,430 --> 01:09:53,450
♫ I want to say this to you ♫

925
01:09:53,450 --> 01:10:01,040
♫  Our time that was filled with excitements ♫

926
01:10:01,040 --> 01:10:04,950
♫ The memory that's shining like you ♫

927
01:10:04,950 --> 01:10:09,290
♫ The world seems to have stopped for a moment ♫

928
01:10:09,290 --> 01:10:14,600
♫ And gets filled with our memories ♫

929
01:10:14,600 --> 01:10:18,910
♫ How do you feel ♫

930
01:10:18,910 --> 01:10:21,250
[Young Lady and Gentleman]

931
01:10:21,250 --> 01:10:23,260
As Ms. Park said, I'm the problem.

932
01:10:23,260 --> 01:10:26,030
- I'm the one who crossed the line.
- Chairman.

933
01:10:26,030 --> 01:10:27,310
Yes, Ms. Park?

934
01:10:27,310 --> 01:10:29,900
This is something you do because you like me.

935
01:10:29,900 --> 01:10:32,120
Please stop hiding your feelings.

936
01:10:32,120 --> 01:10:33,830
And let's just like each other.

937
01:10:33,830 --> 01:10:36,500
Soo Chul, I will disappear like the wind.

938
01:10:36,500 --> 01:10:37,830
At least for Dan Dan's sake.

939
01:10:37,830 --> 01:10:39,150
CEO Anna.

940
01:10:39,150 --> 01:10:41,680
She changed the way she acts toward me.

941
01:10:41,680 --> 01:10:43,400
Why do you need to see her at this point?

942
01:10:43,400 --> 01:10:45,450
I don't know why but that hurts my feelings.

943
01:10:45,450 --> 01:10:47,820
What is she doing? Hey!

944
01:10:47,820 --> 01:10:49,570
What are you doing right now?

945
01:10:49,570 --> 01:10:51,150
- You wench.
- Is that true?

946
01:10:51,150 --> 01:10:53,390
Let's take some time to think about it.

947
01:10:53,390 --> 01:10:54,960
You will get a cold if you get rained on.

948
01:10:54,960 --> 01:10:58,040
Let's just use the umbrella together.

949
01:10:58,040 --> 01:11:00,600
♫ On the street where I still hear that song ♫

950
01:11:00,600 --> 01:11:04,200
♫  I stopped again today and promised to you  ♫
